extends _base.pug

append content
    div(class="content")
        a(title="add to slack" href="https://slack.com/oauth/v2/authorize?client_id=588720890436.589085146405&scope=commands") 
            img(alt="Add to Slack" src="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png" srcset="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png 1x, https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack@2x.png 2x" width="139" height="40")

        h2 Use /markdownlinks to share web addresses that are cleanly formatted using Markdown syntax.

        img(class = "demo-gifs" src="img/demos/safe-demo.gif" alt="demonstration of safe and successful web address formatting")

        h3 If you forget the format for [Markdown](hyperlink syntax), use the /markdownlinks help command to remember.
        img(class = "demo-gifs" src="img/demos/help-demo.gif" alt="demonstration of help option")

        h3 
            | Markdownlinks uses 
            a(class="google-safe-browse" title="Google safe browse home" href="https://safebrowsing.google.com/") Google Safe Browse
            |  to check whether a web address is potentially harmful.
        p Suspicious web addresses are exposed and marked with an emoji representing their threat types.
        ul
            li
                img(class="emoji" src="img/emojis/beetle.png" alt="beetle")
                a(class="google-safe-browse" title="Google safe browse malware" href="https://www.stopbadware.org/")  malware
            li 
                img(class="emoji" src="img/emojis/biohazard_sign.png" alt="biohazard sign")
                a(class="google-safe-browse" title="Google safe browse phishing" href="https://googleonlinesecurity.blogspot.com/2015/11/safe-browsing-protection-from-even-more.html")  phishing/social engineering
            li
                img(class="emoji" src="img/emojis/no_entry_sign.png" alt="no entry sign")
                a(class="google-safe-browse" title="Google safe browse unwanted software" href="https://www.google.com/about/unwanted-software-policy.html")  unwanted software
            li 
                img(class="emoji" src="img/emojis/exclamation.png" alt="exclamation")
                |  potentially harmful application or unspecified threat
        p
            | Web addresses not suspected of being harmful earn a small blue diamond.
            img(class="emoji" src="img/emojis/small_blue_diamond.png" alt="small blue diamond")
        p
            | A small orange diamond 
            img(class="emoji" src="img/emojis/small_orange_diamond.png" alt="small orange diamond")
            | means the web address was
            a(class="google-safe-browse" href="https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/http-vs-https/")  shared without https.
        img(class = "demo-gifs" src="img/demos/harmful-demo.gif" alt="demonstration of harmful yet successful web address formatting")
        p 
            i Google Safe Browse and https checks are not performed on web addresses shared outside of Markdown syntax.

        h3 A warning indicates when Markdownlinks fails to contact Google Safe Browse
        p 
            | Web addresses keep their formatting but do not earn the small blue diamond.
            img(class="emoji" src="img/emojis/small_blue_diamond.png" alt="small blue diamond")
        img(class = "demo-gifs" src="img/demos/error-demo.gif" alt="demonstration of safe yet failed web address formatting")

        h3 Thank you for visiting!
